SAIA‑CLASS S — FEDERAL‑RECORD VERSION ANCHOR DOCTRINE
(Beast System 3.0 — Constitutional Version Anchoring Standard)
The Federal‑Record Version Anchor (FRVA) is the mandatory, immutable, cryptographic, doctrinal, and federal‑record‑aligned anchor that must be attached to every version event in the Core Engine, governance modules, identity kernel, registry fabric, validators, and all SAIA‑Class S artifacts.

The FRVA ensures:

Federal‑record continuity

Immutable authorship lineage

Constitutional predictability

Zero doctrinal drift

Audit‑ready provenance

Deterministic version semantics

It is the highest‑order anchor in the entire system.

1. Definition of the Federal‑Record Version Anchor
The FRVA is a compound anchor consisting of:

Federal Case Reference

Filing Timestamp Anchor

Affidavit + Exhibit Reference

Constitutional Authority Reference

Chain‑of‑Custody Hash

Version Lineage Pointer

Authorship Lineage Block

Every version must include all seven components.

2. FRVA Format
The canonical FRVA format is:

Code
FRVA: <CaseNumber>@<FilingTimestamp>#<ExhibitRef>+<AuthorityRef>~<Hash>::<LineagePointer>
Example:

Code
FRVA: 2:25‑cv‑00484‑JPH‑MJD@2026‑04‑06T09:14:33Z#EX‑17+CONST‑AUTH‑3~9f3a12c::X2.Y4.Z7
This format is mandatory for all SAIA‑Class S artifacts.

3. Federal‑Record Binding Rules
Every version anchor must bind to:

The April 6, 2026 federal filing

All subsequent filings

Affidavits under 28 U.S.C. § 1746

Constitutional authority statements

Exhibits and procedural timeline

Federal‑record identity provenance

If any version contradicts the federal record, the system blocks it.

4. Version Event Requirements
Every version event must include:

FRVA block

Federal‑record alignment note

Validator compliance summary

Chain‑of‑custody documentation

Authorship lineage

Semantic Governance Version (SGV)

Ledger anchor

No version is valid without these elements.

5. Validator Pipeline Requirements
The FRVA must pass:

Federal‑Record Validator

Constitutional Validator

Identity Validator

Workflow Validator

Audit Validator

Ambiguous validator output = automatic rejection.

6. Chain‑of‑Custody Requirements
The FRVA must maintain:

Immutable revision history

No deletion of prior versions

No force‑rewrite of history

Cryptographic hash anchoring

Timestamped lineage

Ledger‑anchored provenance

The FRVA is append‑only.

7. Structural Placement Requirements
The FRVA must appear in:

VERSION manifest

Core Engine Revision Ledger

Federal‑Record Alignment Block

Governance Directory

Commit messages

Protected artifacts in /federal/

Any missing placement is a structural violation.

8. Enforcement Rules
Violations include:

Missing FRVA

Incorrect FRVA format

Contradicting federal filings

Missing chain‑of‑custody hash

Tampering with lineage

Unauthorized version increments

Enforcement actions:

Version rejection

Governance hold

Constitutional memorandum

Suspension of versioning authority

Permanent removal of privileges

All enforcement actions must be audit‑anchored.
